article.headline: CS Bakersfield 77, Long Beach St. 71
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. (AP) -- Trent Blakely had 18 points and five rebounds to lead four players in double figures in Cal State Bakersfield's 77-71 victory over Long Beach State on Saturday night. The Roadrunners (8-17) shot 57 percent from the field in the second half and put the game away with a late 21-8 run. That ended a seesaw game that featured 14 lead changes. Zack Grasmick had 17 points, including four 3-pointers, Terrence Johns added 14 points and Donavan Bragg chipped in with 13 points and five assists. Donovan Morris tallied his fourth 30-plus point game of the season, scoring a game-high 32 for the 49ers (6-18). He hit 11-of-18 from the field while grabbing a team-high eight rebounds. Leading by five points with a little over six minutes remaining, Long Beach State could only muster 2-of-7 shooting down the stretch. Maurice Clady added 17 points for the 49ers while Arturas Lazdauskas scored 12 points to go along with six rebounds. The Roadrunners led 35-34 at the half, but pulled away late in the contest thanks to 9-of-10 shooting from the free throw line in the final two minutes of the game.
